County, Nema clash over dumpsite project The charge sheet indicated that they forged nine documents and illegally obtained Sh350,275. They were also faced with charges of conspiracy to commit a felony and stealing by servant. The court heard that they jointly stole Sh3 million, which was in their possession by virtue of their employment. Through lawyer Davidson Warutere, the suspects demanded to be supplied with copies of witness statements the prosecution will rely on during the trial. The case will be mentioned on August 20, 2018 for a pretrial.